commit.message:
Less unittest and more pytest (#154)

* Don't use unittest when running test files

The commands I used here were:

$ git grep -l unittest.main | xargs sed -i 's/unittest.main()/sys.exit(pytest.main(sys.argv[1:] + [__file__]))/g'
$ git ls-files -m | xargs -I {} sh -c "echo 'import sys\nimport pytest' >> '{}'"
$ isort --float-to-top .

* run unittest2pytest -nw tests

* remove unnecessary unittest

* make flake8 happy
